⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Rod Kimble
node HRD · HRD · ⟦Rod Kimble:HRD:6ae539⟧

WHO   — Rod Kimble — the holy-fool stuntman
WHAT  — The sincere center of the absurdity: a man-child whose total, ridiculous belief is the whole engine of the film and its secret heart.
WHERE — HRD · Hot Rod (2007)  Framework inputs: Hot Rod (2007, dir. Akiva Schaffer, The Lonely Island/Paramount); verified cast & facts  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the comedy is a disguise for the oldest parable — a son who needs his father to see him — and Rod carries it.
HOW   — By committing utterly to the bit, failing, dancing it out, and believing in himself until it stops being a joke.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I believe in myself. Cool beans. My safe word is whiskey — and I'll jump fifteen buses to make my dad proud of me.

